{
  "texts": [
    "The 2CWY+ cluster is strictly associated with the prediction of low gene expression, too.",
    "EPMs of the 2GCB+ cluster, however, identified in A. thaliana, S. bicolor and Z. mays do occur rather up-or downstream of the TSS and TTS region, respectively or, in contrast, within the transcribed region, with conversely regulatory effects (Fig. 4d).",
    "These findings indicate that the linear distance of CREs to their cognate gene plays a defined role in gene regulation.",
    "Interestingly, it has also been demonstrated that most similar to EPMs 2CT+, CT(GA)-binding motifs of paralogous transcription factor BPC6 are localised at the TSS in barley (Hordeum) genes, as well 61.",
    "These TFs are responsive to cytokinin stimulus 61, congruent with findings about BPC6 in response to brassinosteroids in A. thaliana 25."
  ]
}